—ЩLarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/fill.mdЩ@52c95b20106863f8ce6a4fd2e03ff88366cf46f5b086b28438ffa6346b2035ff«title: fill‘ЁExamplesЪFill a string on the left side to a width of 15 with the character 'в”Ђ'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'nushell' | fill --alignment l --character 'в”Ђ' --width 15
nushellв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ

```
Fill a string on the right side to a width of 15 with the character 'в”Ђ'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'nushell' | fill --alignment r --character 'в”Ђ' --width 15
в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђnushell

```
Fill an empty string with 10 'в”Ђ' characters.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '' | fill --character 'в”Ђ' --width 10
в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ

```
Fill a number on the left side to a width of 5 with the character '0'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1 | fill --alignment right --character '0' --width 5
00001

```
Fill a number on both sides to a width of 5 with the character '0'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1.1 | fill --alignment center --character '0' --width 5
01.10

```
Fill a filesize on both sides to a width of 10 with the character '0'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1kib | fill --alignment middle --character '0' --width 10
0001024000

```
’ђђЪCTitle: title: fill
Path: Examples
Content:
Fill a string on the left side to a width of 15 with the character 'в”Ђ'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'nushell' | fill --alignment l --character 'в”Ђ' --width 15
nushellв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ

```
Fill a string on the right side to a width of 15 with the character 'в”Ђ'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'nushell' | fill --alignment r --character 'в”Ђ' --width 15
в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђnushell

```
Fill an empty string with 10 'в”Ђ' characters.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '' | fill --character 'в”Ђ' --width 10
в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ

```
Fill a number on the left side to a width of 5 with the character '0'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1 | fill --alignment right --character '0' --width 5
00001

```
Fill a number on both sides to a width of 5 with the character '0'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1.1 | fill --alignment center --character '0' --width 5
01.10

```
Fill a filesize on both sides to a width of 10 with the character '0'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 1kib | fill --alignment middle --character '0' --width 10
0001024000

```
